@marcusianlevine I'm not able to reproduce this on 1.10.3 - Can you confirm if this is a problem there or only against master?

Classic UI code: https://github.com/apache/airflow/blob/16d93c9e45e14179c7822fed248743f0c3fd935c/airflow/www/templates/airflow/dag.html#L423-L428

RBAC UI code: https://github.com/apache/airflow/blob/16d93c9e45e14179c7822fed248743f0c3fd935c/airflow/www_rbac/templates/airflow/dag.html#L425-L430

An alternative would be for you to subclass the existiing PythonBranchOperator like this in your code base:

```python
class MyBranchOperator(PythonBranchOperator):
    def __int__(**kwargs):
        super().__init__(python_callable=self.choose_branch, **kwargs)

    def choose_branch(self):
        return 'task_a' # etc.
```
